  "text": "The diplotene pairs found in M. luteus are probably a consequence of the germ cell arrangement and interaction, which constitute ''cysts'' with synchronously dividing cell connections via intercellular bridges due to the lack of cytokinesis during spermatogenesis. [CITATION_1] described the presence of similar cysts in the testis of P. phalangiodes.",
